item.description:
A cheatsheet for what git reset does in each mode of operation.
git reset --hard &lt;commit&gt;
Current branch, index, and working directory set to the tree of &lt;commit&gt;.
git reset [--mixed] &lt;commit&gt;
Current branch and index set to the tree of &lt;commit&gt;. Working directory not modified.
git reset --soft &lt;commit&gt;
Current branch set to the tree of &lt;commit&gt;. Index and working directory not modified.

I always forget the proper incantation for creating UTF-8 databases in PostgreSQL. I just had to do this for a project so I&rsquo;m writing it down for future reference. Maybe it&rsquo;ll be useful to somebody else out there.
&lt;code&gt;sudo -u postgres createdb -E UTF8 -T template0 --locale=en_US.utf8 template_utf8&lt;/code&gt;  Now use this UTF-8 &ldquo;template database&rdquo; when creating your project database:
&lt;code&gt;createdb -T template_utf8 new_database&lt;/code&gt;
